	<text id="ruskin_to_joan_july_23_1867">
	    
	    <header>
	        <inventNo>2003L01528</inventNo>
	    </header>
	
	    <body>
	        <div type="text">
	            <pb n="1"/>           
	            <opener>
	                <placeName><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="Q1025076" type="place">Keswick</rs>
	                </placeName>
	                <day>Tuesday</day>
	                <date when="1867-07-23"><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs type="date">23rd 1867</rs>
	                </date>
	                <salute>My dearest wee <rs key="76205504" type="person">Pussy</rs>,</salute><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	            </opener>
	            
	            <p id="p1">
	                <s id="s1">I'm very glad <rs key="k_simson" type="person">Kate</rs> is'nt here! there are very bad <unclear reason="illegible">lessons</unclear> going on in the passage - an innocent husband just called to his wife from his <unclear reason="illegible">dressingroom</unclear></s>
	                <s id="s2">"Where's my lake-Guidebook?"</s>
	                <s id="s3">And the wife replied</s>
	                <s id="s4">"you ought to know!"</s>
	            </p>    
	
	            <p id="p2">    
	                <s id="s5">I've sent you <hi rend="underline">such</hi> a packet of <unclear reason="illegible">
	                    nicest</unclear> letters to-day - I had torn <rs key="m_hilliard" type="person">Mrs. H's</rs>across
	                    then thought
	                    you might like to see it.</s>
	            </p>    
	
	            <p id="p3">    
	                <s id="s6">It's very stingy and naughty of mama to write her poor boy no Sunday letter - He won't be a good boy if he does'nt get Sundays letters.</s>
	                <s id="s7">He'll go and eat too much muffin again.</s>
	            </p>    
	
	            <p id="p4">    
	                <s id="s8">So you're actually going to home to-morrow! you dear nice pussy.</s>
	                <s id="s9">But poor grannie! what is she to do - I shall drink <pb n="2"/> to <rs key="k_simson" type="person">Kate's</rs> health, and good behaviour to-day.</s>
	            </p>
	
	            <p id="p5">    
	                <s id="s10">I wonder where she's going to ????????</s>
	                <s id="s11">- It's raining here - in it's prettiest way - I believe it thinks <del rend="overstrike">it</del> that it's the right thing to do always.</s>
	            </p>    
	            
	            <p id="p6">
	                <s id="s11">I shall write to <rs key="Q66813351" type="place">Denmark Hill</rs> to-morrow.</s>
	            </p>
	
	            <closer>
	                <salute>Ever you loving Cuzzie</salute><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                <signed><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="73859585" type="person">J.R.</rs>
	                </signed>
	             </closer>
	        </div>
	    </body>
